title.narrative: Service providers better equipped to deliver child protection services

description.narrative: Child protection professionals in BiH were equipped with the knowledge and skills on how to maintain and adapt critical child protection services, in particular community-based mental health and psychosocial support, in the context of COVID-19. More than 650 professionals benefitted from training, and more than 60 institutions, including centres for social welfare, received PPE and IT equipment. More than 14,000 children and 2,800 caregivers were reached directly, and more than 250,000 adults and 100,000 children were reached indirectly with various actions. | Status:Met | As-of Date:18/01/2021
